name: Chocolate Chip Energy Bars
author: CHEFROMANO
summary: This recipe is an easy, basic bar, great for breakfasts and snacks on the go. It's easily changed depending on what's in your cupboards! Feel free to experiment and add other ingredients like coconut, almonds, or dried fruits. You can also substitute applesauce for the oil to cut calories and fat.
directions: Mix oats, walnuts, olive oil, chocolate chips, honey, eggs, and vanilla extract together in a large bowl
Press oat mixture firmly into the prepared baking pan
Place pan in a cold oven
Heat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and bake energy bars until heated through, 25 minutes
Cool completely before cutting into squares
